cs.GT, cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.IT, cs.MA 

The paper deals with the problem of bidding in wireless spectrum auctions, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of reinforcement learning approaches to make inferences about opponents suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). The formulation of the problem as a Markov Decision Process and Markov game suggests a connection to information theory (cs.IT) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
